race.description: Beats In The Valley Music Festival 6 Dec Handicap
race.comment: AIR MARSHAL (5) put the writing on the wall last start when he overcame a slow start to power home and get up for third over 1300m at Ballina. Up in grade but drops 4kgs and this slightly longer trip looks perfect at the third run back. SWIFT CHARM (2) settled worse than midfield then made late inroads without threatening when fresh from a spell over 1200m at Port Macquarie last time. Drops back to a far easier race today his second-up record is impressive. EIGHTY EIGHT STARS (6) has found the line with purpose and hasn't been beaten far in his last couple, both in stronger races over 1200m. Getting up to this trip back in a BM74 looks ideal. INTOXEL (10) dropped out last time over 1500m at Port Macquarie in open company. Worth another chance in this more suitable race. SCOTLAND (4) has a tricky gate but is well in after the claim back in a Benchmark race.
